==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epigenesis
<hw>Ep`i*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>epi-</ets> + <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The
theory of generation which holds that the germ is created entirely new,
not merely expanded, by the procreative power of the parents. It is
opposed to the theory of <contr>evolution</contr>, also to
<contr>syngenesis</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epigenesist</ent>⟦br⟧
